n in and of themselves, contemporary scholars recognize that these texts are often the repositories of profound ideas, although they approach them with little guidance from their academic predecessors. The Anonymity of a Commentator aims to provide this guidance, through a close study of one of the most prolific commentary writers in Islamic history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aHadithxCommentariesxHistory and criticism. 0aSufisvBiography. 0aSufismxDoctrines. 0aSunnaxCommentariesxHistory and criticism. 4aArea Studies : Middle East Studies. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Islam. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Sufism. 7aRELIGION / Islam / History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848520140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438485201423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438485201/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles